The information that must be printed on the face of any ticket for admission to an amusement is:

1. The established price of admission; 
2. The amusement tax rate (5%); 
3. The total admission charge (which includes the amusement tax).

This information is based on the retrieved text, specifically Section 303 - Ticket Labeling, which states that the Producer shall cause to be printed clearly on the face of any ticket, receipt or any other token purchased by a patron for the purpose of admission to an amusement the following information:

a. DELINEATING THE AMUSEMENT TAX – for each admission subject to the collection of a tax pursuant to the provisions of Chapter 241, the Producer shall cause to be printed clearly on the face of any ticket, receipt or any other token purchased by a patron for the purpose of admission to an amusement the following information:
1. The established price of admission;
2. The amount paid for food and drink x 10% = THE ADMISSION CHARGE
3. The admission charge x 5% = THE IMPUTED AMUSEMENT TAX
